  <scaffolding>
    <layer level="1" name="Layer 1">
      <focus/>
      <content>Define core terms: Threat, Risk, Portfolio-Level Threat Management (holistic oversight across assets/systems), ERM (integrates cyber risks with business objectives), CSRR (centralized risk repository). Common misconception: Confusing portfolio-level (aggregate/enterprise) with project-level (isolated). Textual concept map: Central 'Portfolio-Level Threat Management' → ERM (overarching), CSRR (tool), Risk Prioritization (process) → NIST Frameworks.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="2" name="Layer 2">
      <focus/>
      <content>Key components: CSRR for tracking risks; Risk Prioritization (likelihood x impact on objectives); Risk Responses (avoid/mitigate/transfer/accept). Relationships: Flowchart - Identify Risks → Document in CSRR → Assess Aggregate Impact → Prioritize → Respond. Link to standards: NIST IR 8286 (ERM integration), NIST IR 8286B (prioritization). Misconception: Treating all risks equally without enterprise objective alignment.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="3" name="Layer 3">
      <focus/>
      <content>Step-by-step from NIST IR 8286B: 1) Populate CSRR with risks from threat intel/sources; 2) Assess impact on enterprise objectives; 3) Prioritize using defined criteria (e.g., heat maps); 4) Select and implement responses. Real-world example: Post-SolarWinds, enterprises used CSRR to prioritize supply chain risks across portfolios. Tools: GRC platforms like RSA Archer.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="4" name="Layer 4">
      <focus/>
      <content>Cross-domain links: Maturity models (e.g., CMMC scaling), automation (SOAR tools for dynamic CSRR updates), ERM integration (FAIR for quantification, ISO 31000). Optimization: Automate prioritization with AI. Case study: Financial firm integrating portfolio threat mgmt. with regulatory compliance (e.g., DORA). Create: Develop scaled implementation roadmap.</content>
    </layer>
  </scaffolding>
